title: Pederson's focus on job, not future as Jags routed
description: Jaguars coach Doug Pederson said after Sunday's 52-6 loss to the Lions that his job status is out of his control.
author: Michael DiRocco

title: Eberflus defends decision to run clock before kick
description: Bears coach Matt Eberflus defended his decision to not run one final play at the end of Chicago's Week 11 loss to the Green Bay Packers to get kicker Cairo Santos closer to the south end zone at Soldier Field.
author: Courtney Cronin

title: Carsley's mission accomplished as foundations laid for Tuchel
description: England interim manager Lee Carsley can reflect on a mission accomplished as he lays the foundations for incoming head coach Thomas Tuchel.

title: Wales suffer record loss in heavy Australia defeat
description: Wales sink to an all-time results low in their 143-year international rugby history with a heavy loss to Australia in Cardiff with Warren Gatland under pressure.

title: Mahomes, Chiefs finally fall as Allen delivers knockout blow for Bills
description: Josh Allen's late 26-yard TD run on fourth down sealed Buffalo's win and handed Kansas City its first loss after a 9-0 start.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Anthony Richardson's return was exactly what he and the Colts should've hoped for
description: Sitting the past couple weeks might seems to have helped Richardson, who threw and ran the ball well on Sunday and is already back looking like the Colts' QB of the future.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: McIlroy locked with Hojgaard and Rozner in Dubai finale
description: Rory McIlroy moved a big step closer to a double Dubai success after taking a share of the lead into the final round of the season-ending DP World Tour Championship.

title: 'Means so much' - McIlroy matches Ballesteros record with Race to Dubai glory
description: Rory McIlroy has officially been confirmed as Race to Dubai champion for a sixth time and third successive year after another consistent season on the DP World Tour.
